HOUSE BILL 1483
J2, J1 6lr2176
By: Delegates Kaiser, Guyton, and Kaufman
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Clinical Professional Counseling – Out–of–State Providers – Use of Telehealth
3 for Continuity of Care
4 FOR the purpose of repealing the authority of the State Board of Professional Counselors
5 and Therapists to issue a temporary telehealth license; exempting certain State
6 licensure requirements for certain individuals who are licensed in another state and
7 who provide counseling through telehealth to clients in the State; and generally
8 relating to clinical professional counseling and telehealth.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Health Occupations
11 Section 17–101(a)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Health Occupations
16 Section 17–101(l) and 17–301
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY repealing
20 Article – Health Occupations
21 Section 17–101(cc) and 17–304.2
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
23 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
24 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
25 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
26 Article – Health Occupations
